-- Iran Sentences American to Death for Spying for Hostile Nation, Fars Says
-- B y   A n d r e w   J .   B a r d e n
-- 2012-01-09T08:22:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-09/iran-sentences-american-to-death-for-spying-for-hostile-nation-fars-says.html
Iran ’s revolutionary court sentenced
Amir Mirzaei Hekmati, an Iranian-U.S. citizen, to death for
spying, state-controlled Fars news agency said.   The court found Hekmati guilty of collaborating with the
intelligence agency of a “hostile nation,” according to the
agency, which cited its reporter.  Hekmati, who was born in  Arizona  in 1983, said he joined
the U.S. military in 2001 after completing high school,
according to an earlier report by Fars.  To contact the reporter on this story:
